The paper deals with analyzing trends in social data and identifying Simpson's paradox, which is a statistical phenomenon that can affect social data analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents a statistical method to identify Simpson's paradox, which involves analyzing and comparing trends in aggregate data and disaggregated subgroups. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), or Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, which are all relevant to statistical analysis and data processing.
